text: 190 New King's Road, Fulham, London Doorway detail 190 New King's Road, also known as Jasmine House, is a Grade II listed house on New King's Road, Fulham, London, built in the late 18th century. It is mentioned by Pevsner as a "late Georgian detached villa, with pretty enriched cornice and doorcase." ==References== ==External links== Category:Grade II listed houses in London Category:Houses in the London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham Category:New King's Road Category:Grade II listed buildings in the London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham Category:Residential buildings completed in the 18th century
